All requests from client applications first reach the API gateway, which then forwards them to respective backend services.
Each API represents a set of operations available to app developers.


Products -Products in API Management bundle one or more APIs and can be either open or protected. protected ones require a subscription key ,
          subscription key can be automatic or require admin approval.
Groups - groups manage the visibilty of products
             2 type Developers - Authenticated developer  and Guests - Unauthenticated developer portal users, such as prospective customers
           with only read access

Developers - developer is a member of one or more groups, and can subscribe to the products that grant visibility to those groups
          developers subscribe to the products and  they're granted the primary and secondary key for the product

Workspaces - allow decentralized API development teams to manage and productize their own APIs,
            central API platform team maintains the API Management infrastructure
            every workspace contains APIs, products, subscriptions, and related entities that are accessible only to the workspace collaborators
            access is controlled thru RBAC
